      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "# Lets get you out of div 4\n\nFirst thing to note is i will be basing qual of eu qual which is top 200\n\n# Estimated qual\nThe estimated qual is around 370-385  points (385 points to be safe)\n\nKey Priorities\n- First things i note about alot of people in this division is that there teams will sometimes take too many fights or just run from every fight. This is not a good mindset, please try to adopt a mindset where you only fight when needed or are going into the fight with legit 70% of advantages such as you have zone,  height, more health, out looted offspawn maybe cause of your loot route etc. These factors are when you take fights. However please do not try to run from fights the moment someone shoots you etc as this will lead to teams to keep pushign you as they will see this move as you being a bad player. \n- In addition it should be an upmost of importance for you to make every endgame in your games here and to play for consistent placements in the endgame of top 5s and aiming to win everygame. I do not want to see you braindead key midgame and then end up with shambles mats etc when you had max mats and a good postion in zone  in the midgame etc.\n- In addion a good fighting note at this level is that people under pressure if you just stand infront of there wall will edit it leaving themselves exposured as they are pancing. I use this strategy alot of times when fighting mid tier players as they are normally fast to edit and exposure themselves with bad edits\n- Futhermore i recommond getting to know your drop spot, what i mean by this is actually practicing your drop spot and getting a loot route for it you can ask for one for free in #\uD83D\uDCA1・route-request or make your own etc. This will allow you to become familliar with your drop spot and knows the ins and outs giving you an advantage over other players + i recommond using the #\uD83D\uDCCC・playing-as-a-team  team template there with your duo.",
